<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="97" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,261,287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="De Marmels, J." box="[672,895,261,287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 78" refId="ref11677" refString="De Marmels, J. (1989) Odonata or dragonflies from Cerro de la Neblina. Academia de las Ciencias Fisicas, Matematicas y Naturales, Caracas, Venezuela, 25, 1 - 78." type="journal article" year="1989">De Marmels (1989)</bibRefCitation>
from Cerro La Neblina, Río Negro Department in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,299,297,323]" name="Venezuela" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="De Marmels, J." box="[309,530,297,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" pagination="439 - 458" refId="ref11714" refString="De Marmels, J. (2004) Heteragrion makiritare sp. nov., with descriptions of hitherto unknown females and larvae of other species from Venezuela (Odonata: Megapodagrionidae, Lestidae). International Journal of Odonatology, 7 (3), 439 - 458. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 13887890.2004.9748230" type="journal article" year="2004">De Marmels (2004)</bibRefCitation>
described the larva. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bota-Sierra, C. A." box="[762,973,297,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" pagination="97 - 100" refId="ref11299" refString="Bota-Sierra, C. A. (2014) Nine new records of Odonata for Colombia from the Orinoco Basin (Lestidae, Calopterygidae, Heteragrionidae, Coenagrionidae, Libellulidae). Notulae Odonatologicae, 8 (4), 97 - 100." type="journal article" year="2014">Bota-Sierra (2014)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[1081,1183,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[1081,1183,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1252,1362,297,323]" name="Colombia" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion country="Colombia" name="Meta" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Meta Department</collectingRegion>
) based on three males and one female. Here we report 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[918,1022,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[918,1022,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion box="[1226,1321,333,359]" country="Colombia" name="Caqueta" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Caquetá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1334,1437,333,359]" country="Colombia" name="Guaviare" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Guaviare</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[198,279,369,395]" country="Colombia" name="Vaupes" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Vaupés</collectingRegion>
Departments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">
The males of this species are small (abdomen around 
<quantity box="[806,887,404,431]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
) with color pattern similar to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName box="[1226,1398,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falvidorsum">H. falvidorsum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daigle" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickorum">H. bickorum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="mitratum" authorityName="mitratum Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[310,556,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mitratum" subSpecies="mitratum">
<emphasis box="[310,556,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. mitratum mitratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1909" box="[761,929,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidorsum">
<emphasis box="[761,929,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. flavidorsum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[982,1153,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">
H. m. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[1050,1153,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitratum">mitratum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
because these two do not present ventrobasal convexity on cerci in mediodorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[831,930,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Figs. 9H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[942,994,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1699,1724]" captionTargetBox="[353,1227,569,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[349,1237,561,1680]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male cerci: H. inca: Orito, Putumayo (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion m. atroterminatum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion m. mitratum: Puerto Berrio, Antioquia (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253598/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">10H</figureCitation>
), and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daigle" authorityYear="2005" box="[1122,1262,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickorum">
<emphasis box="[1122,1262,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. bickorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the distance between bifurcation of medial process and tip of cerci close to one third the length of cerci in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[1213,1316,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[1213,1316,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1333,1423,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1609,1634]" captionTargetBox="[347,1241,380,1588]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[347,1241,380,1588]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male cerci: H. aequatoriale: San Luis, Antioquia (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Hetera- grion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion bariai: Araracuara, Caquetá (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415713/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
), but close to half that distance in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daigle" authorityYear="2005" box="[517,657,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickorum">
<emphasis box="[517,657,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. bickorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[673,763,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1602,1627]" captionTargetBox="[358,1229,489,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[358,1229,489,1582]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male cerci: H. bickorum: Mocoa, Putumayo (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion breweri: Mitú, Vaupés (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion calendulum: Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415715/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Females are also small (abdomen around 
<quantity box="[1250,1323,549,575]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="31.0">31mm</quantity>
) and very similar in color pattern to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[440,559,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breweri">
<emphasis box="[440,559,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. breweri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they differ by the shape of basal teeth of valves in ventral view, rectangular in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[151,271,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breweri">
<emphasis box="[151,271,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. breweri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[287,387,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1720]" captionTargetBox="[375,1210,536,1667]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[367,1220,525,1676]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Female structures: H. bickorum: Araracuara: Caquetá (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion breweri: Mitú, Vaupés (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. Heteragrion calendulum (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253602/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Fig. 13E</figureCitation>
), but rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Marmels" authorityYear="1989" box="[578,680,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bariai">
<emphasis box="[578,680,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">H. bariai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[696,800,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1547,1572]" captionTargetBox="[380,1208,453,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[380,1208,453,1528]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 12. Female structures: H. aequatoriale (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lat- eral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. Heteragrion bariai: Araracuara, Caquetá (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415719/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="97">Fig. 12H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
